data.description:
Home is eligible for a VA Assumable Loan at 3.50% for 350K. Loan is available for veterans and non-veterans; must qualify. 

3 bedrooms 2.5 baths, 1 dining area, a bonus room/ "Man Cave" and tons of upgrades! Exterior features include a sprinkler system, a privacy fence, and charming white limestone design. The kitchen offers granite countertops, stainless steel appliances including a refrigerator, an island, recessed lighting, and a pantry. One casual dining space off of the kitchen and a "Man Cave" off of the living room area that could be used as office as well. The living room has tile floors that carry throughout the foyer, hallways, and formal dining room. The master bedroom is huge and has a bay window, wood floors, pop-up ceiling, and walk-in closet. The master bath offers elevated countertops, a double vanity, walk-in shower, and a soaker tub. The other two bedrooms offer ceiling fans and plenty of closet space. The hallway bathroom is larger than average and has a linen closet. The ½ bath for guests sits in the hallway off of the living area. Community amenities include hike & bike trails. The home also has one of the only sidewalk areas in the neighborhood which makes nightly walks easy for you and the family. The bus stop for school is adjacent from your home as well as the mailboxes.

Freshly painted at the end of 2022, new light fixtures in the hallway, dining room, and entry way, new roof in 2022. Extended walking area in the attic which makes loading and unloading easy. King Kong flooring coating for the garage and patio floor which includes a transferable 15 year warranty.

Refrigerator will convey with the home. Playscape in backyard can also convey with home, buyer's discretion.
